Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[The number of countries and territories reporting confirmed cases of COVID-19 to WHO remains at 215.

Data by country, area, or territory for 30 Aug 2020 can be accessed at https://promedmail.org/wp-content/uploads/world-pdf/WHO%20daily%20tablesAug30_1598819826.pdf.

- The Americas region reported 50.0% of daily case numbers and 61.7% of the daily deaths reported in the past 24 hours, maintaining its position as the most severely affected region, having reported more than 13.1 million cases. The USA and Brazil still dominate, with Argentina, Colombia, Peru, and Mexico very active as well, as are Chile, Bolivia, Honduras, and Guatemala.

- The European region reported 9.2% of daily case numbers and 5.2% of the daily deaths reported in the past 24 hours, and total cumulative cases reported exceed 4.2 million. Spain, Kazakhstan, Belgium, and Sweden did not report any newly confirmed cases to WHO in the past 24 hours so these figures represent weekend artifact with reduced reporting. Among those countries reporting, France dominates followed by Russia, Ukraine, Turkey, Italy, Romania, and the UK.

- The Eastern Mediterranean region reported 4.5% of daily case numbers and 5.3% of the deaths reported in the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of greater than 1.9 million cases. Iraq still dominates followed by Iran, Morocco, Saudi Arabia, Lebanon, Kuwait, the United Arab Emirates, and the Palestinian Authority.

- The African region reported 2.3% of daily case numbers and 5.2% of the deaths reported in the past 24 hours and have reported more than one million cases. South Africa reported the highest number of cases in the last 24 hours followed by Ethiopia, Algeria, Nigeria, Namibia, Cote d'Ivoire, Kenya, and Zambia.

- The Western Pacific region reported 1.9% of daily case numbers and 2.4% of the deaths reported in the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of 0.48 million cases. The Philippines continues to dominate, followed by Japan, South Korea, and Australia.

- The South East Asia region reported 32.1% of the daily newly reported cases and 20.2% of reported deaths in the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of more than 4.0 million cases. India continues to dominate with reports of over 78 000 cases in the past 24 hours, followed by Indonesia, Bangladesh, and Nepal.

Impression: The overall picture by region is basically the same, taking into account the weekend artifact in reporting.

On the Overview tab at the WHO source URL, the epidemic curve of confirmed COVID-19 cases by WHO region, 30 Dec 2019 through 30 Aug 2020, is an excellent visual representation of the epidemic. - Mod.MPP]

